•Chief Femi Fani-Kayode ABUJA – A former Minister of Aviation, Chief Femi Fani-Kayode may be on his way back to the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) six years after he left for the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), The Nation reports. Sources close to him said he met with chairman, Caretaker/Extra-Ordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC) Governor Mai Mala Buni and Kogi State Governor Yahaya Bello at a guest house in Abuja. The closed door meeting, which lasted for about an hour, The Nation learnt, may not be unconnected with fine tuning plans for the return of the former Minister to APC. Fani-Kayode had earlier met with Governor Bello in his Wuse Zone 6 residence in Abuja before he led the former Minister to the party chairman’s guest house. Details shortly… By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja {Sundiata Post} - Former minister of Aviation and a Chieftain of the Peoples Democratic Party, {PD} Chief  Femi Fani-Kayode has asked the Party not to focus its attention on the dead All Progressives Congress {APC} but rather think of who will be a perfect presidential candidate… In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Former Aviation Minister, Femi Fani-Kayode has reacted as President Muhammadu Buhari addressed the released abducted Kankara students in Hausa rather than English language. Fani-Kayode charged President Buhari to treat all Nigerians aaequal if he wants Nigeria to remain one. The PDP chieftain who… In "Top Stories" ABUJA (Sundiata Post) - Chief Femi Fani-Kayode, former minister of aviation and critic of the administration of President Muhammadu Buhari has jubiliated over the decision of Senate President Bukola Saraki to dump the ruling All Progressive Congress (APC) and go back to the main opposition Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). In… In "Local News"